survey_response.review_text: Very good doctor hemalata ma'am, friendly and treatment is too good, good explanation of the issue

Dr. Hemalatha is definitely one of the best orthodontists in Bangalore. I'm undergoing a braces treatment by her and am extremely happy with the progress. 

One of my upper front teeth had chipped off in an accident and I also had multiple wide gaps between them. Before taking her opinion, I consulted 2 other dentists who simply for the sake of making more money, advised me to get a cap by grinding off the half chipped tooth along with the braces treatment. I would have started my treatment at either of them but luckily for me, I decided to take another opinion and booked an appointment at her clinic via Practo. Only she suggested a non-disruptive way of treatment to sustain my natural tooth without compromising on the final outcome. 

She is extremely well spoken and explains everything in a very calm and composed manner. She explained me the entire treatment plan and the challenges one faces with braces. She patiently listened to my every query and cleared all my doubts. It is evident that she really cares about her work and diligently tries to achieve the best possible result. She treats every patient equally and doesn’t haste in her treatment or talks. Unlike other clinics where orthodontists visit once a month, she is available 24-6 at her clinic. It is a great plus point in case of emergencies.

The clinic is very well equipped and the entire experience there is quite decent. The only problem is that appointments don’t start on time and I normally have to wait for a sufficiently large amount of time ranging from 30 minutes to an hour. The fees is a bit on the higher side but in my opinion, is justified for the treatment she offers.
She *** **** ************* *** did a great job explaining everything so I knew what I was getting into. She’s professional and the clinic itself is very well maintained.
Dr Hema makes you feel most comfortable & takes care of the patient needs very well .. she is empathetic towards pain & provides ultimate treatment..

if the wait time can be reduced it would be still nicer.. we feel we need to wait when we come there to the clinic.. please stick on to the time given as we would have left all our work and come over there.. and  + or - 10-15 mns not an issue but we end up waiting more than an hour sometimes !!

Visiting a dentist was a tough decision, I was afraid of those sharp and fast moving equipment’s in the dental clinic.  Dr. Hema Sanjay inspires the utmost confidence by explaining the producer very well, in a crisp and clear manner. All my fears were put to rest and the treatment was a great experience. By the way the clinic environment is very welcoming not to forget the staff.

review_reply.reply_text:
Thank you Mr Manjunath ..
I wish your father , Mr Guruprasad a good oral health & a smile

The  doctor  doesn't  value  the  time  of  patients.  The  appointment  gets  delayed  most  of the time.  Initially the  treatment was good but,  the  treatment  was cut-short without providing  the retainers, despite  making  the  full  payment.  Preferential treatment  is  meted out  to patients.  It is a well established fact  that  retainers have  to be worn  immediately  after the removal  of braces, but  the doctor is  dismissive  about  it.  Overall  had  a very bad  experience.

The Doctor is very knowledgeable and is sensitive to the children's needs. She was able to make suggestions on how we can manage my son's braces better. She helped us with options that minimised the incidence of mouth ulcers (which my son was prone to). 

We would gladly recommend the doctor for anyone looking for braces for their children.

This is nearly the 4th scheduled visit, and in between scheduled visits, have been to her about 3 times for minor corrections.
The best plus point is that She understands our problem in the first instance only. Explains us the procedure that she is performing, give us guideline to expect and follow in the course of her treatment.
Satisfied with her treatment.

A very nice experience. She is always patient enough and hears to the problems, comes with the solution after giving a good thought, and her experience is a added advantage.
This time there was some emergency she had to attend to and therefore we had to wait. Do not mind that - as we have to respect the emergency situations.
